claim.claim-text:
1. A memory structure comprising; 
a) a substrate; 
b) a plurality of bottom word lines overlying the substrate; 
c) a plurality of top word lines overlying the plurality of bottom word lines; 
d) a plurality of bit lines interposed between the plurality of bottom word lines and the plurality of top word lines, wherein each bit line forms a cross point with each bottom word line and each top word line as it crosses between the top word line and the bottom word line; 
e) a first perovskite material region interposed between the plurality of bottom word lines and the plurality of bit lines at each cross point; and 
f) a second perovskite material region interposed between the plurality of top word lines and the plurality of bit lines at each cross point.

8. A method of manufacturing a memory structure comprising the steps of: 
a) providing a semiconductor substrate; 
b) forming a plurality of bottom word lines; 
c) depositing an isolation material overlying the bottom word lines; 
d) etching an opening to the bottom word lines; 
e) depositing a first layer of perovskite material overlying the bottom word lines and the isolation material; 
f) polishing the first layer of perovskite material, whereby perovskite material remains within the opening to form resistive bits; 
g) forming a plurality of bit lines overlying the layer of perovskite material; 
h) depositing an additional isolation material layer overlying the bit lines; 
i) etching another opening to the plurality of bit lines; 
j) depositing a second layer of perovskite material overlying the bit lines and the isolation material; 
k) polishing the second layer of perovskite material, whereby perovskite material remains to form resistive bits; and 
l) forming a plurality of top word lines overlying the layer of perovskite material.

20. A memory structure comprising; 
a) a substrate; 
b) a plurality of bottom word lines overlying the substrate; 
c) a plurality of top word lines overlying the plurality of bottom word lines; 
d) a plurality of bit lines interposed between the plurality of bottom word lines and the plurality of top word lines, wherein each bit line forms a cross point with each bottom word line and each top word line as it crosses between the top word line and the bottom word line; 
e) a first continuous active layer interposed between the plurality of bottom word lines and the plurality of bit lines; and 
f) a second continuous active layer interposed between the plurality of top word lines and the plurality of bit lines.

28. A method of manufacturing a memory structure comprising the steps of: 
a) providing a semiconductor substrate; 
b) forming a plurality of bottom word lines; 
c) depositing a first layer of perovskite material overlying the bottom word lines; 
d) removing the first layer of perovskite material from regions outside a memory array area, whereby the first layer of perovskite material remains within the memory array area; 
e) forming a plurality of bit lines overlying the layer of perovskite material; 
f) depositing a second layer of perovskite material overlying the plurality of bit lines; and 
g) removing the second layer of perovskite material from regions outside the memory array area, whereby the second layer of perovskite material remains within the memory array area.

43. A method of performing a block erase of a shared bit line memory array comprising the steps of: 
a) providing a memory array having top word lines and bottom word lines with bit lines interposed between the top word lines and the bottom word lines to form an upper cross point and a lower cross point where each bit line cross between each top word line and each bottom word line, wherein a resistive bit is formed at each upper cross point and each lower cross point; 
b) grounding all bottom word lines; 
c) ground all top word lines; and 
d) applying an erase voltage to all bit lines.
